The paper deals with learning intuitive physics from image data using neural networks and symbolic reasoning. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of interaction networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper's emphasis on inferring semantic information from raw pixel data suggests a possible connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
